The fascinating thing about Nightmares and Deep Nightmares is that, besides the regeneration factor, they are a lot like Regeneradors and Iron Maidens from RE4. I think there’s some inspiration we can use from those movements, attacks, and abilities.

King Galactix @KingGalactix January 28
Nightmare: - Punch/Claw Attack. These can be for a 3-4 string combo. - Aerial Block and (new) Aerial Kick. Used against player jump and aerial attacks - Spinning Attack, which stuns the player. - Grab attack and bite (new), like an enemy’s QTE for low player health.

King Galactix @KingGalactix January 28
Deep Nightmare: - Punch/Claw Attack. These can be for a 4-5 string combo. - Aerial Block and (new) Aerial Spin - Earthshaker Attack, which stuns the player and launches them in the air - Grab Attack and Bite. - Spike Attack, the enemy charges and hits the player with its spines.

Even w/ their current moveset, you can make the enemy *situation* more complex—what I mean is have certain enemies set things up for OTHER enemies to chime in. Ex: Little Rex does a headbutt, Nightmare follows up w/ a charged punch, then Deep Nightmare does an aerial. - ini
